<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="393" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1338,1581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1447,1473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rocha, Dumas &amp; Nessimian" authorityYear="2017" box="[321,602,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Xiphocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acqualume">
<emphasis box="[321,602,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Xiphocentron acqualume</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an inferior appendage length and the inferior appendage spines similar to the Caribbean species 
<emphasis box="[429,568,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1996" box="[429,564,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Xiphocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixum">X. prolixum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rocha, Dumas &amp; Nessimian" authorityYear="2017" box="[689,842,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Xiphocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acqualume">
<emphasis box="[689,842,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">X. acqualume</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has no mesal sclerite, differing in this character from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1996" box="[151,282,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Xiphocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixum">
<emphasis box="[151,282,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">X. prolixum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its similar species 
<emphasis box="[538,677,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilarino &amp; Calor" authorityYear="2015" box="[538,673,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Xiphocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamakan">X. kamakan</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The species occurs in the 
<collectingRegion box="[967,1043,1519,1545]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Paraná</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1095,1203,1519,1545]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
Basins, with records from the Cerrado of 
<collectingRegion box="[381,531,1555,1581]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[586,651,1555,1581]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Goiás</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[666,751,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1863,1887]" captionTargetBox="[154,1431,186,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-27@11.[151,1436,181,1840]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 39. Geographical distribution of the new species and analyzed species, including new records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407465" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407465/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="393">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
